# Components of a RAG System

## 1. Data Source

The knowledge base that contains your information.

Examples:

- PDF documents
- Word files
- Websites
- CSV files
- SQL databases
- NoSQL databases
- Company documentation
- Research papers

---

## 2. Document Loader

Loads documents into the application.

Examples:

- PDF Loader
- CSV Loader
- Text Loader
- Web Loader
- Directory Loader

---

## 3. Text Splitter

Large documents are divided into smaller chunks before embedding.

Benefits:

- Better retrieval
- Faster search
- Improved context quality

---

## 4. Embedding Model

Converts text into numerical vectors.

Popular embedding models:

- OpenAI Embeddings
- Hugging Face Embeddings
- Sentence Transformers
- Google Embeddings

---

## 5. Vector Database

Stores document embeddings for similarity search.

Popular vector databases:

- FAISS
- Chroma
- Pinecone
- Weaviate
- Milvus
- Qdrant

---

## 6. Retriever

Searches the vector database and returns the most relevant document chunks.

Common retrieval methods:

- Similarity Search
- Semantic Search
- Hybrid Search
- MMR (Maximum Marginal Relevance)

---

## 7. Large Language Model

Uses the retrieved context to generate the final answer.

Examples:

- GPT models
- Claude
- Gemini
- Llama
- Mistral

