# Best Practices

- Use high-quality embeddings.
- Split documents into meaningful chunks.
- Store embeddings in a scalable vector database.
- Retrieve only the most relevant documents.
- Limit prompt size to avoid token overflow.
- Include source citations when possible.
- Continuously update the knowledge base.
- Monitor retrieval quality using LangSmith.

