# RAG vs Fine-Tuning

| Feature | RAG | Fine-Tuning |
|---------|-----|-------------|
| Uses external knowledge | ✅ Yes | ❌ No |
| Updates knowledge easily | ✅ Yes | ❌ Requires retraining |
| Lower cost | ✅ Yes | ❌ Expensive |
| Better for dynamic data | ✅ Yes | ❌ Limited |
| Suitable for private documents | ✅ Yes | ⚠️ Requires training data |

---

# Summary

**RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation)** in LangGraph combines the power of retrieval systems with Large Language Models to deliver accurate, context-aware responses. By retrieving relevant information from external knowledge sources before generating an answer, RAG minimizes hallucinations and keeps responses up to date. LangGraph enhances RAG by providing stateful workflows, memory, conditional logic, tool integration, and agent orchestration, making it an ideal framework for building production-ready AI assistants and knowledge-based applications.
